Ibrahim Magaji, media aide to former governor of Zamfara State, Abdul-azeez Yari, has confirmed a story by SaharaReporters by acknowledging that his principal was flown to the United Kingdom for medical treatment. SaharaReporters had on Saturday reported how Yari, who was in a bad shape medically, was brought to the airport in a wheelchair ahead of a six-hour-long flight to the UK on a British Airways aircraft. Gov. Abdulazizi-Yari of Zamfara State.
THISDAY “Yari is flying to UK on British Airways flight for a medical trip. He was even brought in a wheelchair,” a source at the airport confirmed to SaharaReporters. Reacting to the report, Magaji said his principal was truly flown abroad for medical reasons. He said, “Yes, he is going for a routine medical check in the United Kigdoom. He has been going there to check his troubled leg.



